TECHNICAL DOCUMENTATION - "STELLAR CODEX: LEGACY OF CIVILIZATIONS"
1. OVERVIEW
"Stellar Codex: Legacy of Civilizations" is a sci-fi educational RPG with procedurally generated planetary systems. The player is an archaeologist exploring abandoned worlds of ancient civilizations. Core gameplay loop: planetary exploration, solving scientific puzzles, collecting artifacts.

Development Goals:
Intuitive gameplay (exploration + puzzles)
High replayability through procedural generation
Seamless integration of educational content into gameplay

2. GAME MECHANICS

2.1 Controls and Exploration
Actions: movement, jump (jetpack), scanner, interaction
Ship Hub: orbital management, landing site selection
Physics: variable gravity, vacuum, hazardous environments

2.2 Educational System (Codex)
Disciplines: Astrophysics, Xenobiology, Cryptography
Mechanics: scanning artifacts unlocks encyclopedia entries
Puzzles: based on real scientific principles
Progression: KP (Knowledge Points) for learning new topics

2.3 RPG System

Skills: Scientist, Pilot, Engineer, Linguist
Dialogue: impacts reputation and progression paths

2.4 Threats and Enemies
Threat Types: combat drones, wild fauna, environmental hazards
AI: simple FSM (Patrol, Alert, Attack)
Bosses: ruin guardians with vulnerabilities based on scientific principles

3. PROCEDURAL GENERATION

3.1 Planet Modules
JSON description: type, gravity, atmosphere, threats, points of interest

3.2 Generation Algorithm
Star system generation
POI and resource distribution
Unique quest creation

4. SYSTEMS AND ARCHITECTURE

4.1 Data Formats
planets/*.json - planet modules
codex/*.json - educational articles
quests/*.json - procedural quests

4.2 Save System
Meta-progress: Codex, technologies, reputation
Session progress: saved when returning to ship

5. ART AND SOUND
Style: "pseudo-pixelart" retro-futurism
Sound: atmospheric soundtrack, sci-fi sound effects

6. PERFORMANCE AND PLATFORMS
Target: 60 FPS on PC and consoles
Platforms: PC (Steam), PlayStation, Xbox, Switch

7. MVP
1 star system with 3 planet types
Codex with 2 disciplines (15 entries)
3 puzzle types, basic progression system
Planet generator + basic UI
